<exploration xml:id="warm-preguntasNosotros-asistencia" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Preguntas sobre nosotros: Asistencia</title>

<statement>
  <p>¿Cuántos estamos hoy aquí?</p>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[+++++++++++++++++]</p>
  <p>Sample responses:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>We can line up and then count each person.</li>
    <li>We can have everyone move off the carpet when we count them.</li>
    <li>We can have everyone stand up. When we count each person, they sit down.</li>
  </ul>
</solution>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <prelude> (se pueden mostrar previo al enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>10 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->  
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this warm-up is for students to experience part of the Questions About Us routine. Students continue to engage in this routine throughout the section, focused on answering <q>¿Cuántos estamos hoy aquí?</q>. In this activity students develop ideas for how to keep track of which students have been counted, which will be helpful as students count collections in the next activity. As students share answers to questions such as <q>¿Cómo podemos averiguar cuántos estamos aquí?</q> and <q>¿Conté correctamente los estudiantes?</q> they are beginning to construct viable arguments and attend to precision (MP3, MP6).</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Materiales requeridos de la actividad -->
  <!-- <paragraphs>
